Matplotlib is a popular Python library used for data visualization. It allows you to create static, animated, and interactive plots easily. The most commonly used module in Matplotlib is pyplot, which provides functions similar to MATLAB for plotting.

Installing Matplotlib
To install Matplotlib, use:

    - pip install matplotlib

Importing Pyplot

     - import matplotlib.pyplot as plt


Basic Line Plot

x = [1, 2, 3, 4]
y = [2, 4, 6, 8]
plt.plot(x, y)
plt.title("Line Graph")
plt.xlabel("X-axis")
plt.ylabel("Y-axis")
plt.show()
